g some context tests to inspect this. It’s important to understand what the “normal generated test scaffold” in Forge is, as new tests appear to be based on existing copies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing library setup requirements**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the library, specifically net.sf.ehcache:ehcache-core:2.5.0, needs additional setup beyond the standard generated test scaffold. The existing tests require components like JTA, BTM, and JMS, but the normal scaffold may only include the library and JUnit. If meaningful coverage is needed, it seems like transaction components and disk persistence should be included. I’ll need to review the documentation for Ehcache core about its use with XML config, disk storage, and transaction management to clarify these dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking dependencies for transaction management**\\n\\nI see that the existing build includes JTA, and BTM seems necessary to instantiate the default transaction manager lookup along with the JTA transaction manager in the tests. I’m curious about whether geronimo-jms is transitive from BTM, so I’ll need to check the dependencies for BTM 2.1.4. It’s important to verify these details to ensure everything works smoothly in the tests!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_vUjrzzkewYHcL8sHuT30C7gs|fc_0abb67fb92fcb327016a42ffd6a9a4819783843f61c40a5a15", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nfor coord,path in [('btm','org/codehaus/btm/btm/2.1.4/btm-2.1.4.pom'),('btm201','org/codehaus/btm/btm/2.0.1/btm-2.0.1.pom')]:\n print('---', coord)\n print(urllib.request.urlopen('https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/'+path, timeout=20).read().decode()[:6000])\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3303, "output": 598, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22333, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheW