pdate checks in generated tests, e.g. set system property `net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck=true` and use `updateCheck(false)` or XML `updateCheck=\\\"false\\\"`. For Bitronix-based tests, use a temporary `bitronix.properties` file and set `bitronix.tm.configuration` to it, with `bitronix.tm.disableJmx=true` and `bitronix.tm.journal=null`; clear/shutdown Bitronix state after the test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"ehcache-core also contains Hibernate, servlet, Terracotta, and sizeof-agent integration classes, but those are optional/provided integrations and are not required for meaningful core coverage.\",\n    \"Avoid distributed/Terracotta scenarios unless explicitly targeted; they would require external infrastructure and are not necessary for this issue.\",\n    \"Bitronix is old, so native-image tests should keep its configuration minimal and avoid JMX or persistent journal behavior.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0abb67fb92fcb327016a42ffee0cf48197aa4d138c844bf98d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2078, "output": 1043, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29233, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782775779777, "responseId": "resp_0abb67fb92fcb327016a42ffe43cb08197954aa0d91b9b998c"}}
